middle_memory_text: Where we lived, games, relationships, and moving.
end_memory_text: Game suggestions, COVID, work, and getting in touch after.
rest_of_day_open: Not going to lie I want to try and find this person I just talked to cause she was extremely sweet and I believe she would be a good friend to me and my fiance. If I could I would be talking to them for even longer now as it was a good first experience and I'm still actively thinking about the person I just met for the first time. I hope the rest of the week goes just as well.
critical_positive: Common interests, living conditions, social status, and experiences. Open-minded and liberal I would also put as key factors. When we talked there was a mutual feeling that we were giving an honest try at the task at hand. I had some genuine interest in the person and wanted to know more about them.
critical_negative: I don't know how I can pad this out to 50 words or more. I don't think there was any moment where I felt we weren't seeing eye to eye and our personalities clashed. I only wanted to talk to them more and wish we had more time with each other.

begin_memory_text: Video games! This was easy because he had the gamer-dude headphones on so I asked him about that. I think he was relieved that we had something easy to talk about.
middle_memory_text: We kept talking about video games! We were giving each other recommendations, and I actually did look up the ones he told me about, so that was awesome.
end_memory_text: This is where we should have talked the whole time honestly - talking to another "essential" worker about how we were treated during Covid felt really good. We both talked about trying to work these jobs during Covid and what happened since we had to leave them. I think society has forgotten that they're supposed to love essential workers, so this was nice to talk about.
rest_of_day_open: I have a lot of reading to work on for school, and a really large paper to write. So, I expect I will be stuck in the house for the rest of the week - I would be anyway because of Covid, though. I have a couple Zoom meetings for school, too.
critical_positive: What worked well was having a shared interest in video games. I think it would've been a bit harder to find something to talk about at first without the cue of his headphones. We definitely could've talked about our problems as essential workers more, but that's not an obvious thing since class tends to be invisible :)
critical_negative: Honestly, everything went well! I didn't feel weird about the conversation at all, that boy seemed good at keeping conversation flowing and asking questions, as well as pacing everything. It never got awkward or weird. I would talk to him again, and it's cute that he wants me to talk to his girlfriend. Haha.
